"Architecture": {},
```

The up-shot of making a schema pure JSON is that you could create a `make validate-schemas` command. This would be *very* useful, given that people will be manually messing around with the schemas. The validator could not only validate that the schemas are valid JSON, but it could also validate that the schemas have only valid keywords. We could add other make targets too, like `make format-schemas`. This would let users mess around with the JSON any way they want, and the formatter would automatically re-write the JSON in a standard way.

