@ajtritt can you confirm if this true? My understanding of this is as following:

- In order for data to be defined as a link in a spec it needs to have a unique type, i.e., ``neurodata_type_spec`` needs to be set. However, it does not necessarily have to inherit from ``NWBContatiner``
- Inheriting from ``neurodata_type_inc=NWBContainer`` should however be mentioned in the docs as a best practice as it potentially allows for a bit deeper integration with NWB and allows the type to inherit new features we may add the NWBContainer in the future. 
- In order to integrate a new type with the existing format, e.g., to include as part of a processing module, it will need to inherit from ``NWBContainer`` either directly or by inheriting from another NWB group type.

