For those who need to do the same just use this code to save it (more simple than in the exemple) : 
```
void DepthExporter::export_scan(std::string filename, rs2::frameset &frames) {
    rs2::colorizer color_map;
    color_map.set_option(RS2_OPTION_HISTOGRAM_EQUALIZATION_ENABLED, 1.f);
    color_map.set_option(RS2_OPTION_COLOR_SCHEME, 2.f); // White to Black

    auto depth = frames.get_depth_frame();
    cv::Mat dMat(cv::Size(1280, 720), CV_8UC3, (void*)color_map(depth).get_data());

    cv::imwrite( filename, dMat );
    confirmeSave(filename);
}

```

The playback options you are referring to work at the device level. So you need the device in order to control the playback. Since the pipeline is not extendable to playback functionality, you need to ask it for the device it is using. To do that, you can either take the return value from `auto profile = pipeline.start(...)` or from `auto profile = pipeline.get_active_profile()` and then:
```cpo 
auto dev = profile.get_device();
if(auto p = dev.as<rs2::playback>())
{
    //Use p for playback functionality
}
```
I'm not sure how the pipeline will take the `pause` function since there is a timeout for `wait_for_frames` so make sure you handle that.

